  "prompt": "What is the maximum size for an attachment in Facebook messages?",
  "response": "As of the latest information available, the maximum size for an attachment in Facebook Messenger is **25MB**. This limit applies to most types of files, including photos, videos, and documents.\n\nHowever, there are some exceptions and additional details to keep in mind:\n- **Photos**: Facebook may compress photos to reduce file size.\n- **Videos**: For videos sent through Messenger, the limit may be smaller (around 16MB) if sent directly as a file, but you can share larger videos via links or other methods.\n- **Longer Videos**: Facebook Messenger allows you to share videos up to **50MB** if they are recorded directly within the Messenger app.\n- **Links**: You can share links to larger files hosted on cloud services like Google Drive, Dropbox, or OneDrive.\n\nAlways check Facebook's official guidelines, as these limits are subject to change.",
